<h2>What Is an MCP Server (and Why Should Marketers Care)?</h2>
<p>The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard created by Anthropic in November 2024. It gives AI assistants structured access to external tools and data sources. Think of MCP as a USB port for AI. One standard protocol connects any data source to any AI client.</p>
<p>An MCP server is the connector that sits between your marketing tools and your AI assistant. It translates API calls from Google Ads, HubSpot, or GA4 into a format that Claude or ChatGPT can read and act on.</p>
